120
00:39:16,967 --> 00:39:18,719
This way.

121
00:40:20,527 --> 00:40:21,926
This way.

122
00:40:38,847 --> 00:40:41,839
Anemone 12...

123
00:40:48,527 --> 00:40:50,119
Shit.

124
00:42:44,967 --> 00:42:47,003
A special squad.

125
00:42:54,487 --> 00:42:56,842
No.
- Who then?

126
00:42:56,967 --> 00:42:58,320
Nasser?

127
00:42:58,447 --> 00:42:59,880
There.

128
00:43:06,847 --> 00:43:08,246
Get down.

129
00:44:08,167 --> 00:44:09,919
Fuckers.

130
00:47:52,007 --> 00:47:55,477
Everything ok?
- Yes.

131
00:47:55,607 --> 00:47:58,565
You too?
- Yes.

132
00:48:00,167 --> 00:48:02,476
Our driver is dead.

133
00:49:26,047 --> 00:49:28,163
Police. Don't move.

134
00:49:28,287 --> 00:49:31,006
Who are those guys outside?

135
00:49:31,127 --> 00:49:34,119
Don't move.
- Don't shoot.

136
00:49:34,247 --> 00:49:36,397
Hands up.
- Don't shoot.

137
00:49:36,527 --> 00:49:38,518
Hands on your head.

138
00:49:40,887 --> 00:49:45,165
It's all my fault.
- No, it isn't.

139
00:49:45,287 --> 00:49:48,757
Hands up.
- Calm now.

140
00:49:49,847 --> 00:49:54,045
Take it.
- I'm dying of pain.

141
00:49:56,287 --> 00:49:59,643
I'm scared.
- We're going to make it.

142
00:49:59,767 --> 00:50:02,042
We'll get out of this.

143
00:50:02,167 --> 00:50:06,445
I'm scared. Hold me.
- I'm holding you.

144
00:50:15,247 --> 00:50:16,965
Let me.

145
00:50:20,047 --> 00:50:22,322
Santi?
- I'm here.

146
00:50:22,447 --> 00:50:24,802
Don't move.

147
00:50:28,447 --> 00:50:30,961
Squeeze my hand.

148
00:50:31,087 --> 00:50:34,523
Do you feel anything?
- Nothing.

149
00:50:36,367 --> 00:50:39,279
I'm fucked up.

150
00:50:39,407 --> 00:50:42,319
No, you're not.

151
00:50:42,447 --> 00:50:45,644
I'll be in a wheelchair.

152
00:50:45,767 --> 00:50:48,486
I don't want that.
- I'll stay with you.

153
00:50:48,607 --> 00:50:50,563
I don't want that.
- Stay calm.

154
00:50:50,687 --> 00:50:52,757
I'm so cold.
- You're strong.

155
00:50:52,887 --> 00:50:55,196
I'm so cold.

156
00:50:58,607 --> 00:51:01,280
He's dead.
- No, unconscious.

157
00:51:02,287 --> 00:51:05,006
I swear I won't leave you.

158
00:51:05,127 --> 00:51:07,641
I'll get my first aid kid.

159
00:51:47,407 --> 00:51:50,444
What do those guys outside want?

160
00:51:50,567 --> 00:51:54,116
What do they want?

161
00:51:55,527 --> 00:51:58,758
A prisoner.
- No concern of ours.

162
00:51:58,887 --> 00:52:01,720
Let's leave here.

163
00:52:02,847 --> 00:52:07,159
They probably won't like that.
- That's our problem.

164
00:52:07,287 --> 00:52:10,484
We can't move Nasser like this.

165
00:52:10,607 --> 00:52:13,519
We have to get out of here.
- Selim is right.

166
00:52:13,647 --> 00:52:17,322
If we move him now,
he'll die. Understand?

167
00:52:43,767 --> 00:52:48,363
Nasser is my buddy too.
But he said himself:

168
00:52:48,487 --> 00:52:50,921
If something goes wrong, get out.

169
00:53:00,487 --> 00:53:04,036
Look for yourself,
he's dying.

170
00:53:05,047 --> 00:53:09,598
You should be ashamed.
And you have a short-term memory.

171
00:53:09,727 --> 00:53:12,446
Here are the keys.
Get lost.

172
00:53:12,567 --> 00:53:17,482
What is it? You want to go with him, Nadia?
Run away, cowards.

173
00:53:17,607 --> 00:53:21,885
It's not running away.
- What is it then? I'm staying here.

174
00:53:24,527 --> 00:53:26,518
I'm staying too.

175
00:53:36,887 --> 00:53:39,196
So what are you going to do?

176
00:53:40,727 --> 00:53:43,878
He's not the problem.

177
00:53:44,007 --> 00:53:46,760
That guy in the car is.

178
00:53:46,887 --> 00:53:49,640
He's what they want.

179
00:53:50,167 --> 00:53:52,601
Hey, cop.
- What are you doing?

180
00:53:52,727 --> 00:53:55,321
Let that guy go.
- Never.

181
00:53:55,447 --> 00:53:57,677
Fire, bitch.

182
00:53:57,807 --> 00:54:00,196
Drop your gun.

183
00:54:06,087 --> 00:54:08,078
This way.

184
00:54:14,927 --> 00:54:16,599
Upstairs.

185
00:55:24,007 --> 00:55:26,567
This way.

186
00:55:26,687 --> 00:55:28,040
Inside.

187
00:56:26,927 --> 00:56:29,077
Listen up.

188
00:56:50,967 --> 00:56:54,403
Do you read me, Giovanni?
- Yes.

189
00:56:54,527 --> 00:56:58,042
Someone must have heard the alarm.
- I hope so.

190
00:57:38,607 --> 00:57:40,837
Who are all those dead guys?

191
00:57:58,927 --> 00:58:00,918
He's cold.

192
00:58:02,447 --> 00:58:06,042
It'll be fine.
- I can't feel anything.

193
00:58:07,847 --> 00:58:10,236
He can't move.

194
00:58:11,367 --> 00:58:13,517
Let me know if it hurts.

195
00:58:23,807 --> 00:58:26,799
Santi, let us go home,
please.

196
00:58:26,927 --> 00:58:29,236
You can't move.

197
00:58:29,367 --> 00:58:33,645
I want a blanket.
- I'll get you one.

198
00:58:33,767 --> 00:58:36,235
It's so cold in here.

199
00:58:39,967 --> 00:58:41,923
What's he doing?

200
00:58:43,807 --> 00:58:46,924
Santi, we must get him out of here.

201
00:58:56,487 --> 00:58:59,638
This leads to the canal.
But it's very narrow.

202
00:58:59,767 --> 00:59:04,238
He's an incredible acrobat,
both in the air and underground.

203
00:59:04,367 --> 00:59:06,517
Isn't that right, Martial ?

204
00:59:27,367 --> 00:59:30,120
Are you hurt? Let me see.

205
00:59:32,607 --> 00:59:37,920
Your friend isn't going to make it.
He must be somewhere warm and quiet.

206
00:59:38,047 --> 00:59:41,926
In the control room.
Your wound isn't serious.

207
00:59:42,047 --> 00:59:44,117
This is for him.

208
01:00:42,807 --> 01:00:45,162
Giovanni?

209
01:00:45,287 --> 01:00:48,120
How much ammo have you got left?

210
01:00:48,247 --> 01:00:51,159
Look outside. What do you see?

211
01:00:54,247 --> 01:00:56,966
Nothing. Why?

212
01:00:57,087 --> 01:00:59,999
They removed their casualties.

213
01:01:05,727 --> 01:01:11,085
From a distance it seems like
nothing is going on here.

214
01:01:17,287 --> 01:01:20,165
Giovanni agrees
to give them weapons.

215
01:01:20,287 --> 01:01:23,518
Only you can decide that.

216
01:01:23,647 --> 01:01:29,324
I'm asking your opinion.
- Giovanni and I are not allowed to have one.

217
01:01:33,767 --> 01:01:38,761
Don't hide behind orders
like that bulletproof mask.

218
01:01:38,887 --> 01:01:41,321
You're getting emotional.

219
01:01:43,327 --> 01:01:45,363
Fuck you.

220
01:02:03,367 --> 01:02:07,679
You're all going to die.
Understand?

221
01:02:09,367 --> 01:02:11,722
They'll kill you.

222
01:02:12,767 --> 01:02:17,318
You don't frighten me.
I won't have mercy on you either.

223
01:02:17,447 --> 01:02:19,677
A woman...

224
01:02:25,407 --> 01:02:27,523
can you handle this?

225
01:02:27,647 --> 01:02:29,365
Give me.

226
01:02:34,847 --> 01:02:38,044
It's all hands on deck.
Take it.

227
01:02:42,327 --> 01:02:45,080
And no joking around.

228
01:02:45,207 --> 01:02:48,916
